OL,7,FThere is also a suggestion that a
OL,8,Fcenturies-old legal tool - a requete -
OL,9,Fto publicly challenge the position of
OL,10,FDeputy Ozouf.
OL,12,FIf 10 parishioners lodge the requete,
OL,13,Fthen the Constable of the parish would
OL,14,Fhave to call a public meeting, where
OL,15,Fthe people of the parish could make
OL,16,Ftheir opinions known.
OL,18,FA requete can not force him out of
OL,19,Foffice, but it would put politicians
OL,20,Fin no doubt about what parishioners
OL,21,Fthink.
